<HEADLINE>
Wacker Chemie buys out joint ventures with Air Products
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FRANKFURT, Germany 2007-12-11 14:48:50 UTC
</P>
<P>
Chemical company Wacker Chemie AG said Tuesday it will buy out
its two joint ventures with Air Products and Chemicals Inc. in an
effort to strengthen its global polymers business.
</P>
<P>
The two ventures are Air Products Polymers and Wacker Polymer
Systems. Completion of the deal, which is subject to regulatory
approval, is expected in the first quarter of 2008.
</P>
<P>
"Wacker expects that the acquisition will provide strategic
advantages to its global construction-polymers business," the
company said in a statement. "Benefits include synergies and cost
advantages."
</P>
<P>
Wacker will retain the Vinyl Acetate Ethylene activities of the
joint venture, while Air Products will receive full ownership in
the Elkton, Maryland, and Piedmont, South Carolina, production
facilities and their related businesses plus cash considerations
of US$265 million (euro180.62).
</P>
<P>
Wacker shares rose 0.2 percent to euro183.15 (US$268.77) in
Frankfurt.
</P>
